 CoopAfrica promotes the development of cooperatives in Africa (from ICT
Update)
 The Cooperative Facility for Africa - CoopAfrica - is a technical cooperat=
ion
programme for the promotion of cooperative development in Africa. From the
International Labour Organization=B4s (ILO) office in Dar-es-Salaam, CoopAf=
rica
covers nine countries in Eastern and Southern Africa with support of the ILO
cooperative programme in Geneva. Together with a wide range of international
and national partners, CoopAfrica promotes an enabling legal and policy
environment, effective cooperative unions and federations as well as
demand-driven services for cooperatives.
 See:
<http://www.ilo.org/public/english/employment/ent/coop/africa/index.htm>http
://www.ilo.org/public/english/employment/ent/coop/africa/index.htm
