              <b>GM crops deliver a wide range of benefits</b><b> (from
Crop Protection=20
              Monthly)<br>
              </b>Two new studies show that GM crops continue to deliver
significant=20
              global economic and environmental benefits and make
important contributions=20
              to global food production, food security and lower real
prices for=20
              food and feed crops. Graham Brookes, director of PG
Economics, co-author=20
              of the reports, says: =93The technology has also made
important contributions=20
              to increasing crop yields, reducing production risks,
improving=20
              productivity and raising the global production of key
crops. The=20
              combination of economic and environmental benefits is
making a valuable=20
              contribution to improving the sustainability of global
agriculture=20
              and affordability of food. This contribution is greatest in
developing=20
              countries.=94<br>
