              <b>CoopAfrica promotes the development of cooperatives in
Africa=20
              (from ICT Update)</b><br>
              The Cooperative Facility for Africa - CoopAfrica - is a
technical=20
              cooperation programme for the promotion of cooperative
development=20
              in Africa. From the International Labour Organization=B4s
(ILO) office=20
              in Dar-es-Salaam, CoopAfrica covers nine countries in
Eastern and=20
              Southern Africa with support of the ILO cooperative
programme in=20
              Geneva. Together with a wide range of international and
national=20
              partners, CoopAfrica promotes an enabling legal and policy
environment,=20
              effective cooperative unions and federations as well as
demand-driven=20
              services for cooperatives.<br>
              See: <a
href=3D"http://www.ilo.org/public/english/employment/ent/coop/africa/index.=
htm"
target=3D"_blank">http://www.ilo.org/public/english/employment/ent/coop/afr=
